      "content": "hey i was looking at my mortgage statement from wells fargo and im a bit confused. i have a 30 year fixed at 6.5%. if i look at my payments in year 5 vs year 25, why does it feel like my balance barely moves at first? can u explain how the interest vs principal split actually works over time?",
